{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Purpose_for_Us_All",
  "title": "A Purpose for Us All",
  "summary": "In the white-stone Chianar Plaza on New Alderaan, the free-spirited Shael complains to the officer Rasi about being shot at in a shopping district -- piloting and tree-climbing are fun, getting shot at is not. They spot the former Imperial Commodore, the doctor Lynae Cassius, arriving with her watchful escort Vengan, and go to present themselves. A frank conversation unfolds about the Empire, vigilance, and old loyalties, joined by the Sullustan Enb'Zik (Ikihsa), who has history with Lynae and whose keen hearing draws him over from a nearby construction site. Enb'Zik presses Lynae with talk of democracy, compromise as the middle ground between love and fear, and the will of the governed, while Lynae -- bred to fight the war and weary of signing death certificates -- counters with hard-won realism about how rarely people care. As the Force whispers something to Enb'Zik, he quietly observes that Lynae does not speak like an Imperial, a remark that visibly unsettles her. The exchange ends with Enb'Zik bowing to take his leave, warning that a government ruling through fear brings mistrust upon itself, and Lynae accepting his parting words.",
